message.content:
1. The treatment occurred between April 2014 and January 2015.
2. Sixty-nine patients were treated.
3. The patients had 74 HCCs in total.
4. The patients were randomly treated with RFA.
5. RFA was performed using either internally cooled-wet (ICW) electrodes or SC electrodes.
6. ICW electrodes were used in SB mode.
7. SC electrodes were used in SM mode.
8. The treatment with ICW electrodes in SB mode is referred to as SB-RFA.
9. The treatment with SC electrodes in SM mode is referred to as SM-RFA.
10. Thirty-six patients were treated with SB-RFA.
11. Thirty-eight patients were treated with SM-RFA.
